-- China Plans Measures to Curb Rising Food Prices, China Business Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-07T23:39:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-07/china-plans-measures-to-curb-rising-food-prices-china-business-reports.html
Several Chinese government
departments are planning measures to curb rising food prices,
the China Business reported, citing an unidentified official at
the National Development and Reform Commission.  Prices rose for 24 products out of 31, including
vegetables, meat and fruit, in 36 Chinese cities last month,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
